        <hl1>Spinning A-Rod</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''All Those Who Wanted A-Rod Gone, Raise Your Hand,'' April 22: George Vecsey is certainly correct in implying that the Yankees are fortunate not to have traded Alex Rodriguez.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''All Those Who Wanted A-Rod Gone, Raise Your Hand,'' April 22: George Vecsey is certainly correct in implying that the Yankees are fortunate not to have traded Alex Rodriguez.</p>
        <p>He might have also noted that had Rodriguez been traded and begun his season with 12 home runs in 15 games, doubters would have said that he never would have done as well if subjected to the pressure of playing for the Yankees.</p>
        <p>Lonnie Hanauer  West Orange, N.J.</p>
      </block>
